{{Quote|The power of the dark side resides in that lake, Nomi Sunrider. Do not listen to it.|Master Thon|audio=LakeNatth-TOTJ.flac|<ref name="Tales of the Jedi (audio)">[[Tales of the Jedi (audio drama)|''Tales of the Jedi'' audio drama]]</ref>}}
'''Lake Natth''' was a [[lake]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Ambria/Legends|Ambria]].

==History==
After [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Thon]] defeated [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] [[Force ghost/Legends|spirits]] that threatened to take the sector, he contained their [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]] energy beneath the lake. Over time, the power of the dark side warped the creatures of the lake, resulting in the creation of the vicious [[Hssiss]].

During the [[Cold War (Galactic Republic–Sith Empire)|Cold War]] between the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and the [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|reconstituted Sith Empire]], there were unusual evidences for life close to the lake discovered.<ref name="Mission">{{TORcite|type=crewskill|Bioanalysis|Poison Planet}}</ref>

While waiting for a meeting between himself and [[Dark Lord of the Sith/Legends|Lord]] [[Skere Kaan]], [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]] made camp along its shores, something those native to Ambria never did, as they gave the lake a wide berth.

Through meditation, a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] could draw minerals out of the lake and infuse them with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to create the [[Luxum]] crystal. This crystal was powerful against droids, releasing an ion pulse upon contact.

